# Introduction

This is a primitive version of reserbot. This bot tries to learn natural languages learning from imitation. 
Now, it is possible to try to teach knowledge using an artificial language called tokipona:

"Toki Pona is a simple language designed to express the most, using the least. The entire language has only 123 words 
and 14 sounds. The grammar, although different from English, is very regular and easy to learn." 
(from http://en.tokipona.org/wiki/What_is_Toki_Pona%3F)

# Requirements (so far):
 * Python 2.7 (I'm not sure about other versions)
 * Oger (http://reservoir-computing.org/organic/engine)

# How to use it:

 ./start.sh tokipona --interface console
 
or
 
 ./start.sh tokipona --interface jabber  --user JABBERUSER --pass PASSWORD --jid JID

or

 ./start.sh --help

# Example session
In this example session reserbot is taught to:
* say pona if you say toki (at first of the conversation)
* say nasa if you say telo (at first of the conversation)

--> load
Loading bootstrapped neurosequencers.
Loading src/languages/tokipona/bootstrapped_data/seqLetterSyllable
Loading src/languages/tokipona/bootstrapped_data/seqSyllableWord
Loading src/languages/tokipona/bootstrapped_data/seqWordPhrase
Loading src/languages/tokipona/bootstrapped_data/seqWordSyllables
Loading src/languages/tokipona/bootstrapped_data/seqSyllableLetters
Loading src/languages/tokipona/bootstrapped_data/seqPhraseWords
--> start
Conversation started.
--> say toki .
Processing "toki ."
<== momisisnmn         
--> say pona .
Processing "pona ."
<==           
--> end
Conversation ended.
--> start
Conversation started.
--> say telo .
Processing "telo ."
<== msissim         
--> say nasa .
Processing "nasa ."
<==           
--> end
Conversation ended.
--> rest
Resting ...
(wait please)
Done.
--> start
Conversation started.
--> say toki .
Processing "toki ."
<== pona  . 
--> discard
Conversation aborted.
--> start
Conversation started.
--> say telo .
Processing "telo ."
<== nasa  . 
--> quit
bye!

